text: Donholm is a settlement in Kenya's Nairobi Area. Donholm's name comes from a colonial Kenya land/plantation owner James Kerr Watson (3 October 1881-11 November 1955), who gave the name "Donholm" to his dairy farm in the area.Donholm has various Estates including: Harambee Sacco, Phase 5, Old Donholm, New Donholm and Phase 8 -- which also hold various Courts. == References == Category:Populated places in Nairobi Province
title: Doonholm
